                  <a href="/genre/cape-breton-fiddling/">Cape Breton Fiddling</a>
                  <p>Distinctive Celtic fiddling originating from the Scottish immigrants who settled in Canada on Cape Breton Island.</p>
               </div>
         
         
            </li>
         </ul>
         
            </li>
         </ul>
         
            </li>
         </ul>
                  
         <ul class="hierarchy_list">
            <li class="hierarchy_list_item">
               <div class="hierarchy_list_item_details">
                  <a href="/genre/french-canadian-folk-music/">French-Canadian Folk Music</a>
                  <p>Brought by French colonists to their Nouvelle-France settlements, primarily based around French Folk Music with influences from English Folk Music and Celtic Folk Music, typically played during gatherings and holidays.</p>
               </div>
         
         
            </li>
         </ul>
                  
         <ul class="hierarchy_list">
            <li class="hierarchy_list_item">
               <div class="hierarchy_list_item_details">
                  <a href="/genre/metis-fiddling/">Métis Fiddling</a>
                  <p>Canadian style blending First Nations and European musical influences into an up-tempo style of fiddling characterized by the use of syncopation and indigenous rhythms.</p>
